(509, 'Exercise Response', 'Fat loss response to exercise', '155', 'ADRB3', 'AG', 'The ADRB3 gene encodes for a protein (Î²3-adrenergic receptor - Î²3-ADR), which is mainly located in the fat tissue and to a certain extent in the muscle tissue. This protein plays a role in regulating fat breakdown and production of body heat. Variations', 'https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed?LinkName=gene_pubmed&from_uid=155', 'rs4994', 3),
